<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1882,1988]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
The most recent family diagnosis for the 
<taxonomicName box="[629,772,1882,1908]" class="Malacostraca" family="Epimeriidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Epimeriidae</taxonomicName>
is that of 
<bibRefCitation author="Coleman" box="[886,1229,1882,1908]" pageId="1" pageNumber="37" refString="Coleman, C. O. &amp; Barnard, J. L. (1991) Revision of Iphimediidae and similar families (Amphipoda: Gammaridea). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 104, 253 - 268." type="journal article" year="1991">
Coleman and Barnard (
<number box="[1158,1221,1882,1908]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" value="1991.0">1991</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, and 
<bibRefCitation author="Barnard" pageId="1" pageNumber="37" refString="Barnard, J. L. &amp; Karaman, G. S. (1991) The families and genera of marine gammaridean Amphipoda (except marine Gammaroidea). Records of the Australian Museum, Supplement 13, Part 1, 1 - 417, Part 2, 418 - 866." type="book chapter" year="1991">
Barnard and Karaman (
<number box="[275,337,1922,1948]" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" value="1991.0">1991</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, respectively. The first volume of 
<emphasis box="[753,1398,1923,1948]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">
Synopsis of benthic 
<taxonomicName box="[989,1124,1923,1948]" class="Malacostraca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Amphipoda</taxonomicName>
of the Southern Ocean
</emphasis>
by Charles Oliver Coleman, including a key to the 
<collectingCountry box="[711,820,1962,1988]" name="Antarctica" pageId="1" pageNumber="24">Antarctic</collectingCountry>
species of 
<taxonomicName box="[951,1098,1962,1988]" class="Malacostraca" family="Epimeriidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Epimeriidae</taxonomicName>
, will be published shortly.
</paragraph>
